55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.1843619f-c385-4ab5-afba-44ccabc8e313.description=
Gets the string value of an LDAP objects named property.
Creates a collection if more than one property of the same name exists.
Continue to call this same operation for all values until No More Values is returned.

Input Parameters\:
host - Name or IP address of LDAP server to query.
DN - DN of object to get property.
propertyName - Name of property to get.
username - Name of user to connect to LDAP as.
password - Password of user.
useADAuth - Add this input and set to false if using a non AD LDAP server. If false, uses ServerBind instead of secure NTLM based bind.
port - Specify the port in case it is not the default one, or it is not specified in the host path.

Responses\:
value retrieved - The value was retrieved and set as the result (returnResult).
no more values - There are no more values in the collection.
failure - failed to complete operation (one of the reasons could be port validation failure).

55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.412fa840-6291-40f7-88d3-63a844800db8.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.547e4ad4-8390-4725-b7f0-4d37f92db4d1.description=
The flow will  find a group (groupDNToFind) in a group (groupDNToStart)'s parent groups recursively. For example, OODevSubGroup2 is a member of OODevSubGroup1. OODevSubGroup1 is a member of OODevGroup. It should be able to find OODevGroup in OODevSubGroup2's parent groups. It is intended to be used as a sub flow for "Is User in Group".

Inputs\:
host - The hostname of an active directory domain controller.
username - The username for host.
password - The password for the username.
groupDNToFind - The DN of the group to find, for example \: CN\=OODevGroup,OU\=OODevTest,DC\=battleground,DC\=ad.
groupDNToStart - The DN of the group to search for its parent groups, for example\: CN\=OODevSubGroup2,OU\=OODevTest,DC\=battleground,DC\=ad.

Responses\:
success - The groupDNToFind is one of the parent groups of the groupDNToStart.
failure - The groupDNToFind is not one o f the parent groups of  the groupDNToStart.
55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.5f9b8b69-30d0-4401-9900-039957280485.description=Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings Inputs\: operator - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=). value1 - the first value. value2 - the second value. Returns\: The result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false. Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true. failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false. 55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.86e55ab4-5470-4a44-9517-81087e3f952a.description=Converts a list of numerical fields into a base 10 number. Inputs\: list - A list of numbers in the given base. delimiter - the delimiter for list. startIndex - The index to start reading the list from. Default is 0. endIndex - The index to start reading the list from. Default is end. base - The number base to convert from. Use 256 for bytes. reverse - A boolean value that reverses the list before processing it. If a list is not reversed bytes towards the end of the list are more significant than bytes towards the start. Returns\: The converted number. Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. failure - Something went wrong. 55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.a327a7e3-b603-4134-932e-e36f3a6c9aeb.description=
Compares two strings lexigraphically.

Inputs\:
String1 - The first string.
String2 - The string to compare string 1 to.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true' then the compare is not case sensitive.

responses\:
before - If string 1 is alphabetically before string 2.
after - If string 1 is alphabetically after string 2.
same - If string 1 is alphabetically equal to string 2.
failure - If Something goes wrong.

55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.afa44943-d201-4fb5-9f7d-7dcd7e96730e.description=
Checks if a user is in an active directory group.

Inputs\:
host - the hostname of an active directory domain controller.
username - username for host.
password - password for username.
userDN - The DN of the user to check, for example\: CN\=John Doe,CN\=Users,DC\=MyDomain,DC\=com
groupDN - The DN of the group to check, for example\: CN\=Domain Users,CN\=Users,DC\=myDomain,DC\=com

Responses\:
success - The userDN is a member of the groupDN
failure - the userDN is not a member of the groupDN
55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.description=
Checks if a user is in an Active Directory group. The group can have the specified user as a direct member or can be the ancestor of such a group.

Inputs\:
host - The hostname of an Active Directory domain controller.
username - The username for host.
password - The password for the username.
userDN - The DN of the user to check, for example\: CN\=John Doe,CN\=Users,DC\=Domain,DC\=com
groupDN - The DN of the group to check, for example\: CN\=Domain Users,CN\=Users,DC\=Domain,DC\=com

Responses\:
success - The userDN is a member of the groupDN.
failure - The userDN is not a member of the groupDN or an error occurred.
55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.ec229f39-d1c8-4a1c-8585-925b52f39a98.prompt=Distinguished Name\: 55346d0e-efc8-4c4f-8436-5fd5ef7d391f.f503f252-c9b4-456e-b543-cb75b1f60e32.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
